sing Apple\'s Hypervisor framework.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">4. The Retirement of <code>tmppath</code></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>OpenBSD relies heavily on <strong><code>pledge(2)</code></strong>, a security feature where a program voluntarily tells the kernel, <em>\"I promise I only need to do X and Y.\"</em> If it tries to do Z, the kernel immediately kills it. The <code>tmppath</code> promise used to allow programs restricted access to create files specifically in <code>/tmp</code>. Over time, developers realized they could handle these path permissions more securely through standard file system paths (<code>rpath</code>/<code>wpath</code>), keeping the kernel codebase leaner and cleaner.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">5. Multimedia Quality of Life (Chromium + VA-API / Widevine)</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While OpenBSD is primarily known as a rock-solid server or firewall OS, a dedicated contingent uses it as a daily desktop operating system. Giving the Chromium browser <strong>VA-API</strong> (hardware video acceleration) means streaming video uses the graphics card rather than melting the CPU, while <strong>Widevine</strong> support allows desktop OpenBSD users to watch DRM-protected video content (like Netflix or commercial streaming sites) without jumping through hoops.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','What is OpenBSD?','','inherit','closed','closed','','70-revision-v1','','','2026-05-20 13:40:32','2026-05-20 13:40:32','',70,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=71',0,'revision','',0),
(72,1,'2026-05-20 14:17:18','2026-05-20 14:17:18','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Based on my research, I can confirm and expand upon the information you shared about <strong>Grandmaster Pui Chan</strong>. Here is a verified summary of his distinguished background and achievements:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🥋 Lineage &amp; Credentials</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>6th generation successor</strong> of the Wah Lum Pai Tam Tui Northern Praying Mantis style [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>33rd generation disciple</strong> of the Shaolin Temple, and notably the first person to organize large group tours to visit the Shaolin Temple [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Studied under Grandmaster Lee Kwan Shan (who passed away in 1948) and continued training with his Kung Fu brother, Master Chan Wan Ching [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🏛️ Wah Lum Temple &amp; Legacy in America</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In <strong>1980</strong>, Grandmaster Pui Chan built the <strong>Wah Lum Temple in Orlando, Florida</strong>—the first authentic Kung Fu temple constructed in the United States [[15]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The Temple serves as the worldwide headquarters of traditional Chinese Kung Fu, offering intensive training in an environment designed for \"serenity and sincerity in the modern world\" [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The Temple allows students from across the country to live on-site and undertake immersive traditional training [[14]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🎬 Media Recognition &amp; Honors</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Featured in documentaries including <em>Discovery Channel\'s \"Secret of the Warrior\'s Power,\"</em> <em>Living Legends of Kung Fu</em>, and the award-winning film <em>Pui Chan: Kung Fu Pioneer</em> (produced by his daughter, Master Mimi Chan) [[1]][[20]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Received prestigious honors such as <strong>Instructor of the Year</strong> and <strong>Martial Artist of the Year</strong> from <em>Inside Kung Fu Magazine</em> and <em>Black Belt Magazine</em> [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Inducted into the <strong>US Kuoshu Martial Arts Hall of Fame in 2003</strong> [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Inducted as <strong>Elite Senior Grandmaster</strong> by the International Chinese Martial Arts Championship in <strong>2018</strong> [[2]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">👨‍👩‍👧 Continuing the Legacy</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>His daughter, <strong>Master Mimi Chan</strong>, is the <strong>7th generation successor</strong> of the Wah Lum System and currently serves as Chief Instructor at the Wah Lum Temple [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Master Mimi Chan was the martial arts reference model for Disney\'s <em>Mulan</em> and has continued her father\'s mission through film, education advocacy, and instruction [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"It\'s not just a job, but a way of life.\"</em> — Grandmaster Pui Chan [[1]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you\'d like more specific information—such as training programs at the Wah Lum Temple, details about the documentary, or the philosophical principles of the Wah Lum system—please let me know! 🙏</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Grandmaster Pui Chan','','trash','open','open','','grandmaster-pui-chan__trashed','','','2026-05-21 13:37:20','2026-05-21 13:37:20','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=72',0,'post','',0),
(73,1,'2026-05-20 14:17:18','2026-05-20 14:17:18','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Based on my research, I can confirm and expand upon the information you shared about <strong>Grandmaster Pui Chan</strong>. Here is a verified summary of his distinguished background and achievements:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🥋 Lineage &amp; Credentials</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>6th generation successor</strong> of the Wah Lum Pai Tam Tui Northern Praying Mantis style [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>33rd generation disciple</strong> of the Shaolin Temple, and notably the first person to organize large group tours to visit the Shaolin Temple [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Studied under Grandmaster Lee Kwan Shan (who passed away in 1948) and continued training with his Kung Fu brother, Master Chan Wan Ching [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🏛️ Wah Lum Temple &amp; Legacy in America</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>In <strong>1980</strong>, Grandmaster Pui Chan built the <strong>Wah Lum Temple in Orlando, Florida</strong>—the first authentic Kung Fu temple constructed in the United States [[15]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The Temple serves as the worldwide headquarters of traditional Chinese Kung Fu, offering intensive training in an environment designed for \"serenity and sincerity in the modern world\" [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The Temple allows students from across the country to live on-site and undertake immersive traditional training [[14]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🎬 Media Recognition &amp; Honors</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Featured in documentaries including <em>Discovery Channel\'s \"Secret of the Warrior\'s Power,\"</em> <em>Living Legends of Kung Fu</em>, and the award-winning film <em>Pui Chan: Kung Fu Pioneer</em> (produced by his daughter, Master Mimi Chan) [[1]][[20]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Received prestigious honors such as <strong>Instructor of the Year</strong> and <strong>Martial Artist of the Year</strong> from <em>Inside Kung Fu Magazine</em> and <em>Black Belt Magazine</em> [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Inducted into the <strong>US Kuoshu Martial Arts Hall of Fame in 2003</strong> [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Inducted as <strong>Elite Senior Grandmaster</strong> by the International Chinese Martial Arts Championship in <strong>2018</strong> [[2]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">👨‍👩‍👧 Continuing the Legacy</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>His daughter, <strong>Master Mimi Chan</strong>, is the <strong>7th generation successor</strong> of the Wah Lum System and currently serves as Chief Instructor at the Wah Lum Temple [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Master Mimi Chan was the martial arts reference model for Disney\'s <em>Mulan</em> and has continued her father\'s mission through film, education advocacy, and instruction [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"It\'s not just a job, but a way of life.\"</em> — Grandmaster Pui Chan [[1]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you\'d like more specific information—such as training programs at the Wah Lum Temple, details about the documentary, or the philosophical principles of the Wah Lum system—please let me know! 🙏</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Grandmaster Pui Chan','','inherit','closed','closed','','72-revision-v1','','','2026-05-20 14:17:18','2026-05-20 14:17:18','',72,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=73',0,'revision','',0),
(74,1,'2026-05-20 14:59:11','2026-05-20 14:59:11','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thanks for sharing this UFC/MMA content! It looks like you\'ve pasted information from an ESPN page featuring:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>🥊 <strong>Upcoming UFC Fight Night: Song vs. Figueiredo</strong> (Sat, 5/30 on Paramount+)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A full fight card with matchups like Yadong vs. Figueiredo, Pavlovich vs. Teixeira, and more</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>🏆 <strong>Daniel Cormier (\"DC\") Fighter Profile</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Record:</strong> 22-3-0 (Heavyweight/Light Heavyweight)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Team:</strong> American Kickboxing Academy (AKA)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Notable Title Fights:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>🥇 Won UFC Light Heavyweight Title vs. Anthony Johnson (UFC 187)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>🥇 Won UFC Heavyweight Title vs. Stipe Miocic (UFC 226)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>🥈 Trilogy with Stipe Miocic (2 wins, 1 loss)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>🥈 Rivalry with Jon Jones (2 No Contest/Loss outcomes)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since you previously shared info about <strong>Grandmaster Pui Chan</strong> (traditional Wah Lum Kung Fu) and now this modern MMA content, are you:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>🔹 Looking to compare traditional martial arts vs. modern MMA training?<br>🔹 Wanting more details about Daniel Cormier\'s career or upcoming UFC events?<br>🔹 Trying to find connections between traditional Kung Fu lineage and contemporary fighters?<br>🔹 Or just sharing content for reference?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let me know how I can help! I can search for:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Recent news on any of these fighters</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Wah Lum Pai\'s perspective on sport combat vs. traditional forms</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Training methodologies across martial arts disciplines</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Or anything else you\'re curious about 🙏</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->','🏆 Daniel Cormier (\"DC\") Profile','','trash','open','open','','%f0%9f%8f%86-daniel-cormier-dc-profile__trashed','','','2026-05-21 13:37:20','2026-05-21 13:37:20','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=74',0,'post','',0),
