(107,1,'2026-05-20 21:21:08','2026-05-20 21:21:08','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>National Public Data (NPD) Breach - Complete Overview</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>📍 Company Information</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Legal Name:</strong> Jerico Pictures, Inc. (doing business as National Public Data)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Location:</strong> Florida-based data broker</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Business:</strong> Background checks and employee screening services</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Current Status:</strong> Filed Chapter 11 bankruptcy October 2, 2024; shut down completely by December 2024 [[14]][[16]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>🚨 Breach Timeline</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Event</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>December 2023</strong></td><td>Initial breach began - hackers exploited plaintext password vulnerabilities [[1]][[9]]</td></tr><tr><td><strong>April 2024</strong></td><td>Stolen data appeared on dark web; hacker \"USDoD\" offered data for $3.5 million [[3]][[5]]</td></tr><tr><td><strong>August 2024</strong></td><td>Public disclosure; class action lawsuits filed [[11]]</td></tr><tr><td><strong>August 16, 2024</strong></td><td>Company confirmed breach affecting data from December 2023 through summer 2024 [[1]][[9]]</td></tr><tr><td><strong>October 2, 2024</strong></td><td>Chapter 11 bankruptcy filing [[14]]</td></tr><tr><td><strong>December 2024</strong></td><td>Company completely shut down [[16]]</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Critical Issue:</strong> 8-month delay between breach discovery and public notification [[10]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>📊 Scale of the Breach</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Records Exposed: 2.9 BILLION records</strong> [[6]][[7]][[11]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Data Types Compromised:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Full names</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Current and past addresses (historical data spanning decades)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ <strong>Social Security Numbers (SSNs)</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Dates of birth</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Phone numbers</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Relative/family member information</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Criminal records</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Employment history [[6]][[7]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Geographic Scope:</strong> United States, United Kingdom, and Canada [[7]][[23]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Important Note:</strong> While 2.9 billion <em>records</em> were exposed, this doesn\'t mean 2.9 billion <em>people</em> were affected. The records include multiple entries per person (historical addresses, relatives, etc.). Estimates suggest <strong>up to 170 million individuals</strong> may be affected [[10]].</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>⚖️ Legal Actions &amp; Bankruptcy</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Class Action Lawsuits:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>3 class-action lawsuits</strong> filed in August 2024 [[11]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>14+ federal complaints</strong> filed [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Lead case:</strong> Christopher Hofmann v. Jerico Pictures [[8]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Filed in:</strong> Southern District of Florida [[8]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Allegations Include:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Negligence in data security practices</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Breach of fiduciary duty</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Unjust enrichment from monetizing personal data</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Failure to implement basic security measures (passwords stored in <strong>plaintext</strong>) [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Bankruptcy Impact:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Company faces potential liability \"for credit monitoring for hundreds of millions of potentially impacted individuals\" [[14]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Victims may receive ZERO compensation</strong> due to company insolvency [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bankruptcy petition was later dismissed, but company remains defunct [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Regulatory Actions:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>California Privacy Protection Agency (CPPA):</strong> $46,000 fine for failing to register as a data broker [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Multiple state attorneys general:</strong> Investigations ongoing [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>💰 Settlement Reality</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>❌ No Settlement Announced</strong> - Due to bankruptcy, victims face significant challenges:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Company is insolvent</strong> - No assets to fund compensation</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>No operational entity</strong> - Company shut down December 2024</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Alternative pathways being explored:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>State attorney general settlements (may proceed independently)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Individual suits against data purchasers who bought NPD information</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Identity theft insurance claims for documented losses [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Comparison to Other Breaches:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equifax (2017):</strong> $425M settlement, company remained operational</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>T-Mobile (2021):</strong> $350M settlement</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>NPD:</strong> $0 likely recovery due to bankruptcy [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>🔍 How to Check If You\'re Affected</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Since most victims never knew NPD had their data</strong> (they aggregated from public records without consent), check:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>HaveIBeenPwned.com</strong> - Now includes NPD breach data [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>AnnualCreditReport.com</strong> - Review all three credit reports</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Look for indicators:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Historical addresses (not just current)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Family member information linked to your SSN</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Background check-related inquiries you didn\'t initiate [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>🛡️ What Florida Residents Should Do NOW</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Immediate Actions (24-48 hours):</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ <strong>Place a CREDIT FREEZE</strong> with all three bureaus:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Equifax: 1-800-685-1111</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Experian: 1-888-397-3742</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>TransUnion: 1-800-916-8800</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ <strong>Set up fraud alerts</strong> (free, lasts 1 year)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ <strong>Check credit reports</strong> at AnnualCreditReport.com</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ <strong>Change passwords</strong> on accounts using exposed email addresses</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Within 1-4 Weeks:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Enroll in IRS <strong>Identity Protection PIN</strong> (prevents tax fraud)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Document any suspicious activity</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Consider identity theft monitoring services</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Ongoing (LIFETIME):</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Keep credit freezes active</strong> (unfreeze only when applying for credit)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Annual credit report reviews</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Monitor financial accounts quarterly</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>SSNs cannot be changed</strong> - this is permanent exposure [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>🏛️ Florida-Specific Resources</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Florida Data Breach Notification Law:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Requires companies to notify Florida residents of breaches</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>NPD failed to comply within reasonable timeframe [[44]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Florida Office of the Attorney General:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Report identity theft</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>File complaints about data breaches</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Florida Department of Legal Affairs:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Consumer protection division handles privacy violations</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>❓ Key FAQ</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Q: If NPD is bankrupt, will I receive any compensation?</strong><br><strong>A:</strong> Likely <strong>no direct compensation</strong> from the company. However:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>State AG settlements may create victim funds</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Documented identity theft losses may be recoverable through other means</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Individual suits against data purchasers (not NPD) may be possible [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Q: How is this different from Equifax?</strong><br><strong>A:</strong> Critical differences:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Equifax remained operational and funded $425M settlement</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>NPD declared bankruptcy and shut down</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>NPD stored passwords in <strong>plaintext</strong> (extreme negligence)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Most NPD victims never knew the company existed [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Q: How long should I monitor my identity?</strong><br><strong>A:</strong> <strong>LIFETIME</strong> - SSNs cannot be changed. Experts recommend:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Permanent credit freezes</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Annual credit monitoring</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Ongoing fraud alerts</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>This is now a permanent part of your financial security routine [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>📞 Expert Quotes</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"If people weren\'t taking precautions in the past, which they should have been doing, this should be a five-alarm wake-up call for them.\"<br><strong>— Teresa Murray, Consumer Watchdog Director</strong> [[10]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"We will litigate and bring enforcement actions when businesses violate California\'s privacy laws.\"<br><strong>— Michael Macko, CPPA Head of Enforcement</strong> [[10]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>🔗 Resources</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Check breach status:</strong> HaveIBeenPwned.com</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Credit reports:</strong> AnnualCreditReport.com</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Identity theft reporting:</strong> IdentityTheft.gov</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>IRS IP PIN:</strong> IRS.gov/IdentityTheft</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Bottom Line:</strong> This is one of the largest data breaches in history, affecting potentially every American with an SSN. As a Florida resident, you should assume your data was exposed and take <strong>permanent protective measures</strong> - especially credit freezes. Compensation is unlikely, making prevention your only reliable defense.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Would you like help with specific steps to protect yourself, or do you have questions about any aspect of this breach?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','National Public Data (NPD) Breach','','trash','open','open','','national-public-data-npd-breach__trashed','','','2026-05-21 13:37:00','2026-05-21 13:37:00','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=107',0,'post','',0),
(108,1,'2026-05-20 21:21:08','2026-05-20 21:21:08','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>National Public Data (NPD) Breach - Complete Overview</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>📍 Company Information</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Legal Name:</strong> Jerico Pictures, Inc. (doing business as National Public Data)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Location:</strong> Florida-based data broker</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Business:</strong> Background checks and employee screening services</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Current Status:</strong> Filed Chapter 11 bankruptcy October 2, 2024; shut down completely by December 2024 [[14]][[16]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>🚨 Breach Timeline</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Event</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>December 2023</strong></td><td>Initial breach began - hackers exploited plaintext password vulnerabilities [[1]][[9]]</td></tr><tr><td><strong>April 2024</strong></td><td>Stolen data appeared on dark web; hacker \"USDoD\" offered data for $3.5 million [[3]][[5]]</td></tr><tr><td><strong>August 2024</strong></td><td>Public disclosure; class action lawsuits filed [[11]]</td></tr><tr><td><strong>August 16, 2024</strong></td><td>Company confirmed breach affecting data from December 2023 through summer 2024 [[1]][[9]]</td></tr><tr><td><strong>October 2, 2024</strong></td><td>Chapter 11 bankruptcy filing [[14]]</td></tr><tr><td><strong>December 2024</strong></td><td>Company completely shut down [[16]]</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Critical Issue:</strong> 8-month delay between breach discovery and public notification [[10]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>📊 Scale of the Breach</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Records Exposed: 2.9 BILLION records</strong> [[6]][[7]][[11]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Data Types Compromised:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Full names</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Current and past addresses (historical data spanning decades)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ <strong>Social Security Numbers (SSNs)</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Dates of birth</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Phone numbers</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Relative/family member information</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Criminal records</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ Employment history [[6]][[7]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Geographic Scope:</strong> United States, United Kingdom, and Canada [[7]][[23]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Important Note:</strong> While 2.9 billion <em>records</em> were exposed, this doesn\'t mean 2.9 billion <em>people</em> were affected. The records include multiple entries per person (historical addresses, relatives, etc.). Estimates suggest <strong>up to 170 million individuals</strong> may be affected [[10]].</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>⚖️ Legal Actions &amp; Bankruptcy</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Class Action Lawsuits:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>3 class-action lawsuits</strong> filed in August 2024 [[11]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>14+ federal complaints</strong> filed [[1]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Lead case:</strong> Christopher Hofmann v. Jerico Pictures [[8]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Filed in:</strong> Southern District of Florida [[8]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Allegations Include:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Negligence in data security practices</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Breach of fiduciary duty</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Unjust enrichment from monetizing personal data</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Failure to implement basic security measures (passwords stored in <strong>plaintext</strong>) [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Bankruptcy Impact:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Company faces potential liability \"for credit monitoring for hundreds of millions of potentially impacted individuals\" [[14]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Victims may receive ZERO compensation</strong> due to company insolvency [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Bankruptcy petition was later dismissed, but company remains defunct [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Regulatory Actions:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>California Privacy Protection Agency (CPPA):</strong> $46,000 fine for failing to register as a data broker [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Multiple state attorneys general:</strong> Investigations ongoing [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>💰 Settlement Reality</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>❌ No Settlement Announced</strong> - Due to bankruptcy, victims face significant challenges:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Company is insolvent</strong> - No assets to fund compensation</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>No operational entity</strong> - Company shut down December 2024</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Alternative pathways being explored:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>State attorney general settlements (may proceed independently)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Individual suits against data purchasers who bought NPD information</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Identity theft insurance claims for documented losses [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Comparison to Other Breaches:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Equifax (2017):</strong> $425M settlement, company remained operational</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>T-Mobile (2021):</strong> $350M settlement</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>NPD:</strong> $0 likely recovery due to bankruptcy [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>🔍 How to Check If You\'re Affected</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Since most victims never knew NPD had their data</strong> (they aggregated from public records without consent), check:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>HaveIBeenPwned.com</strong> - Now includes NPD breach data [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>AnnualCreditReport.com</strong> - Review all three credit reports</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Look for indicators:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Historical addresses (not just current)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Family member information linked to your SSN</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Background check-related inquiries you didn\'t initiate [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>🛡️ What Florida Residents Should Do NOW</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Immediate Actions (24-48 hours):</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ <strong>Place a CREDIT FREEZE</strong> with all three bureaus:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Equifax: 1-800-685-1111</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Experian: 1-888-397-3742</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>TransUnion: 1-800-916-8800</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ <strong>Set up fraud alerts</strong> (free, lasts 1 year)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ <strong>Check credit reports</strong> at AnnualCreditReport.com</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>✅ <strong>Change passwords</strong> on accounts using exposed email addresses</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Within 1-4 Weeks:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Enroll in IRS <strong>Identity Protection PIN</strong> (prevents tax fraud)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Document any suspicious activity</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Consider identity theft monitoring services</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Ongoing (LIFETIME):</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Keep credit freezes active</strong> (unfreeze only when applying for credit)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Annual credit report reviews</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Monitor financial accounts quarterly</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>SSNs cannot be changed</strong> - this is permanent exposure [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>🏛️ Florida-Specific Resources</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Florida Data Breach Notification Law:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Requires companies to notify Florida residents of breaches</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>NPD failed to comply within reasonable timeframe [[44]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Florida Office of the Attorney General:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Report identity theft</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>File complaints about data breaches</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Florida Department of Legal Affairs:</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Consumer protection division handles privacy violations</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>❓ Key FAQ</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Q: If NPD is bankrupt, will I receive any compensation?</strong><br><strong>A:</strong> Likely <strong>no direct compensation</strong> from the company. However:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>State AG settlements may create victim funds</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Documented identity theft losses may be recoverable through other means</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Individual suits against data purchasers (not NPD) may be possible [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Q: How is this different from Equifax?</strong><br><strong>A:</strong> Critical differences:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Equifax remained operational and funded $425M settlement</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>NPD declared bankruptcy and shut down</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>NPD stored passwords in <strong>plaintext</strong> (extreme negligence)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Most NPD victims never knew the company existed [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Q: How long should I monitor my identity?</strong><br><strong>A:</strong> <strong>LIFETIME</strong> - SSNs cannot be changed. Experts recommend:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Permanent credit freezes</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Annual credit monitoring</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Ongoing fraud alerts</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>This is now a permanent part of your financial security routine [[10]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>📞 Expert Quotes</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"If people weren\'t taking precautions in the past, which they should have been doing, this should be a five-alarm wake-up call for them.\"<br><strong>— Teresa Murray, Consumer Watchdog Director</strong> [[10]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"We will litigate and bring enforcement actions when businesses violate California\'s privacy laws.\"<br><strong>— Michael Macko, CPPA Head of Enforcement</strong> [[10]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>🔗 Resources</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Check breach status:</strong> HaveIBeenPwned.com</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Credit reports:</strong> AnnualCreditReport.com</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Identity theft reporting:</strong> IdentityTheft.gov</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>IRS IP PIN:</strong> IRS.gov/IdentityTheft</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Bottom Line:</strong> This is one of the largest data breaches in history, affecting potentially every American with an SSN. As a Florida resident, you should assume your data was exposed and take <strong>permanent protective measures</strong> - especially credit freezes. Compensation is unlikely, making prevention your only reliable defense.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Would you like help with specific steps to protect yourself, or do you have questions about any aspect of this breach?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','National Public Data (NPD) Breach','','inherit','closed','closed','','107-revision-v1','','','2026-05-20 21:21:08','2026-05-20 21:21:08','',107,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=108',0,'revision','',0),
(109,1,'2026-05-20 22:53:08','2026-05-20 22:53:08','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gennady Zyuganov’s article frames a highly specific, state-aligned vision of a changing world order, heavily utilizing the ideological and philosophical rhetoric championed by the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) and the Kremlin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The piece serves as an analytical defense of Chinese President Xi Jinping’s <strong>Global Governance Initiative (GGI)</strong>, which was introduced at the historic Shanghai Cooperation Organization (SCO) summit in Tianjin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Decoding Zyuganov\'s Analysis of the 5 Principles</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zyuganov translates Xi Jinping’s conceptual framework into the Russian Communist Party\'s strategic worldview. He breaks down how these principles are intended to function:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Sovereign Equality:</strong> Zyuganov argues that the \"house rules\" of a select few Western nations should not be imposed globally. This principle asserts that a nation’s wealth or military power should not dictate its voting weight or voice in global affairs.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>The Rule of International Law:</strong> The text heavily emphasizes adherence to the UN Charter as a defense mechanism. Zyuganov frames this as a guardrail to stop what he calls the \"law of the jungle,\" criticizing the U.S. and NATO for bypassing international consensus.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>A \"New\" Multilateralism:</strong> Rather than tearing down the United Nations, this principle advocates for reforming existing global institutions from within. The goal is to strip away unilateral veto powers or structural biases that favor the West, adapting them to modern realities.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>A Human-Centered Approach:</strong> This principle targets the socioeconomic gap between the Global North and the Global South. Zyuganov highlights that global governance should focus on practical quality-of-life improvements—such as resource distribution, economic stability, and poverty reduction—rather than what he describes as \"abstractly declaring\" Western-style rights and freedoms.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>A Focus on Action:</strong> Zyuganov emphasizes that China does not just present theoretical concepts, but backs them with heavily capitalized infrastructure platforms like the Belt and Road Initiative, the Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank (AIIB), and the BRICS New Development Bank.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Geopolitical Reality Behind the Rhetoric</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While Zyuganov relies on classical Marxist-Leninist terminology (\"imperialism,\" \"global oligarchy,\" \"reactionary forces\"), the context of the article is deeply anchored in a unified front between Moscow and Beijing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The piece highlights the <strong>\"Joint Declaration of the Russian Federation and the People\'s Republic of China on the Establishment of a Multipolar World and a New Type of International Relations,\"</strong> which was signed in Beijing by Vladimir Putin and Xi Jinping during Putin\'s high-profile state visit. This strategic alignment—described by Chinese Foreign Minister Wang Yi as being \"as stable as a mountain\"—presents the Moscow-Beijing axis as a direct counterweight to Western economic sanctions and diplomatic isolation, particularly in light of ongoing global conflicts, such as the escalated tensions and warfare surrounding Iran.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ultimately, Zyuganov\'s piece is less about standard communist theory and more about a pragmatic, institutional pivot. He positions the SCO and BRICS as the core pillars of a brand-new global framework designed to permanently end Western hegemony.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can watch this video report on <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=djxW6isw9XU\">Putin and Xi\'s Multipolar World Order Declaration</a> to see news coverage of the summit where the leaders signed the historic declaration mentioned by Zyuganov.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Gennady Zyuganov','','trash','open','open','','gennady-zyuganov__trashed','','','2026-05-21 13:37:00','2026-05-21 13:37:00','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=109',0,'post','',0),
(110,1,'2026-05-20 22:53:08','2026-05-20 22:53:08','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gennady Zyuganov’s article frames a highly specific, state-aligned vision of a changing world order, heavily utilizing the ideological and philosophical rhetoric championed by the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) and the Kremlin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The piece serves as an analytical defense of Chinese President Xi Jinping’s <strong>Global Governance Initiative (GGI)</strong>, which was introduced at the historic Shanghai Cooperation Organization (SCO) summit in Tianjin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Decoding Zyuganov\'s Analysis of the 5 Principles</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zyuganov translates Xi Jinping’s conceptual framework into the Russian Communist Party\'s strategic worldview. He breaks down how these principles are intended to function:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Sovereign Equality:</strong> Zyuganov argues that the \"house rules\" of a select few Western nations should not be imposed globally. This principle asserts that a nation’s wealth or military power should not dictate its voting weight or voice in global affairs.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>The Rule of International Law:</strong> The text heavily emphasizes adherence to the UN Charter as a defense mechanism. Zyuganov frames this as a guardrail to stop what he calls the \"law of the jungle,\" criticizing the U.S. and NATO for bypassing international consensus.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>A \"New\" Multilateralism:</strong> Rather than tearing down the United Nations, this principle advocates for reforming existing global institutions from within. The goal is to strip away unilateral veto powers or structural biases that favor the West, adapting them to modern realities.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>A Human-Centered Approach:</strong> This principle targets the socioeconomic gap between the Global North and the Global South. Zyuganov highlights that global governance should focus on practical quality-of-life improvements—such as resource distribution, economic stability, and poverty reduction—rather than what he describes as \"abstractly declaring\" Western-style rights and freedoms.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>A Focus on Action:</strong> Zyuganov emphasizes that China does not just present theoretical concepts, but backs them with heavily capitalized infrastructure platforms like the Belt and Road Initiative, the Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank (AIIB), and the BRICS New Development Bank.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Geopolitical Reality Behind the Rhetoric</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While Zyuganov relies on classical Marxist-Leninist terminology (\"imperialism,\" \"global oligarchy,\" \"reactionary forces\"), the context of the article is deeply anchored in a unified front between Moscow and Beijing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The piece highlights the <strong>\"Joint Declaration of the Russian Federation and the People\'s Republic of China on the Establishment of a Multipolar World and a New Type of International Relations,\"</strong> which was signed in Beijing by Vladimir Putin and Xi Jinping during Putin\'s high-profile state visit. This strategic alignment—described by Chinese Foreign Minister Wang Yi as being \"as stable as a mountain\"—presents the Moscow-Beijing axis as a direct counterweight to Western economic sanctions and diplomatic isolation, particularly in light of ongoing global conflicts, such as the escalated tensions and warfare surrounding Iran.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ultimately, Zyuganov\'s piece is less about standard communist theory and more about a pragmatic, institutional pivot. He positions the SCO and BRICS as the core pillars of a brand-new global framework designed to permanently end Western hegemony.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can watch this video report on <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=djxW6isw9XU\">Putin and Xi\'s Multipolar World Order Declaration</a> to see news coverage of the summit where the leaders signed the historic declaration mentioned by Zyuganov.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Gennady Zyuganov','','inherit','closed','closed','','109-revision-v1','','','2026-05-20 22:53:08','2026-05-20 22:53:08','',109,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=110',0,'revision','',0),
