(141,1,'2026-05-21 03:22:14','2026-05-21 03:22:14','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here is a complete breakdown of everything regarding the track <strong>\"SKYLINE\"</strong>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Track Overview</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Release Date:</strong> August 27, 2021</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Length:</strong> 2 minutes and 57 seconds</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Label:</strong> Released independently under <strong>Husla Music</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Genre:</strong> German Hip-Hop / Street Rap with a melodic, atmospheric vibe.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Behind the Scenes &amp; Production</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The track brought together some highly active names in the European production scene to give it a cinematic, nighttime soundscape:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Producers:</strong> <strong>Jurij Gold</strong> and <strong>Falconi</strong> (frequent collaborators known for engineering dark, heavy-bass, and atmospheric beats for major German rap artists).</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Mastering:</strong> Engineered by ChrisKlangquartier.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Visuals:</strong> The official music video was directed and shot by <strong>Benny 030</strong>, a prominent videographer in the Berlin rap scene.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Power Trio (The Artists)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The song functions as a unique crossover because all three artists bring completely different legacies to the table:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Massiv (Wasiem Taha):</strong> A literal giant in German gangsta rap. Originally breaking out in the mid-2000s out of Berlin-Wedding (and known for his label <em>Al Massiva</em>), he is famous for his incredibly deep voice, imposing physical presence, and aggressive street anthems. Beyond music, he gained massive mainstream fame playing the character \"Latif\" in the critically acclaimed TNT/Netflix series <em>4 Blocks</em>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Crackaveli:</strong> A highly respected veteran of the Berlin underground rap scene. He has been putting out gritty street rap since the late 2000s, often collaborating with artists like Kalusha, Mosh36, and the late street-rap pioneer Deso Dogg.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Yasha (Yasha Conen):</strong> The secret weapon on the track\'s hook. Yasha is a singer and producer best known for providing the iconic, soulful vocals on the diamond-certified 2012 mega-hit <strong>\"Lila Wolken\"</strong> alongside Marteria and Miss Platnum. His melodic, airy style serves as the perfect contrast to the heavy street bars of Crackaveli and Massiv.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What the Song is About</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>True to its title, <em>SKYLINE</em> plays on the contrast of looking up at the high-rise city skylines from the concrete blocks below. It leans heavily into themes of late-night reflection, street hustle, loyalty to the grid, and chasing success while staying grounded in the urban environments that raised them. Yasha’s melodic chorus gives it a driving, almost melancholic late-night driving anthem feel, while Crackaveli and Massiv anchor it with rugged, raw verses.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','CRACKAVELI x MASSIV x YASHA - SKYLINE','','trash','open','open','','crackaveli-x-massiv-x-yasha-skyline-official-video__trashed','','','2026-05-21 13:37:00','2026-05-21 13:37:00','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=141',0,'post','',0),
(142,1,'2026-05-21 03:22:14','2026-05-21 03:22:14','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here is a complete breakdown of everything regarding the track <strong>\"SKYLINE\"</strong>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HwqR\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HwqR\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Track Overview</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Release Date:</strong> August 27, 2021</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Length:</strong> 2 minutes and 57 seconds</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Label:</strong> Released independently under <strong>Husla Music</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Genre:</strong> German Hip-Hop / Street Rap with a melodic, atmospheric vibe.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Behind the Scenes &amp; Production</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The track brought together some highly active names in the European production scene to give it a cinematic, nighttime soundscape:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Producers:</strong> <strong>Jurij Gold</strong> and <strong>Falconi</strong> (frequent collaborators known for engineering dark, heavy-bass, and atmospheric beats for major German rap artists).</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Mastering:</strong> Engineered by ChrisKlangquartier.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Visuals:</strong> The official music video was directed and shot by <strong>Benny 030</strong>, a prominent videographer in the Berlin rap scene.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Power Trio (The Artists)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The song functions as a unique crossover because all three artists bring completely different legacies to the table:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Massiv (Wasiem Taha):</strong> A literal giant in German gangsta rap. Originally breaking out in the mid-2000s out of Berlin-Wedding (and known for his label <em>Al Massiva</em>), he is famous for his incredibly deep voice, imposing physical presence, and aggressive street anthems. Beyond music, he gained massive mainstream fame playing the character \"Latif\" in the critically acclaimed TNT/Netflix series <em>4 Blocks</em>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Crackaveli:</strong> A highly respected veteran of the Berlin underground rap scene. He has been putting out gritty street rap since the late 2000s, often collaborating with artists like Kalusha, Mosh36, and the late street-rap pioneer Deso Dogg.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Yasha (Yasha Conen):</strong> The secret weapon on the track\'s hook. Yasha is a singer and producer best known for providing the iconic, soulful vocals on the diamond-certified 2012 mega-hit <strong>\"Lila Wolken\"</strong> alongside Marteria and Miss Platnum. His melodic, airy style serves as the perfect contrast to the heavy street bars of Crackaveli and Massiv.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What the Song is About</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>True to its title, <em>SKYLINE</em> plays on the contrast of looking up at the high-rise city skylines from the concrete blocks below. It leans heavily into themes of late-night reflection, street hustle, loyalty to the grid, and chasing success while staying grounded in the urban environments that raised them. Yasha’s melodic chorus gives it a driving, almost melancholic late-night driving anthem feel, while Crackaveli and Massiv anchor it with rugged, raw verses.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','CRACKAVELI x MASSIV x YASHA - SKYLINE (OFFICIAL VIDEO)','','inherit','closed','closed','','141-revision-v1','','','2026-05-21 03:22:14','2026-05-21 03:22:14','',141,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=142',0,'revision','',0),
