(199,1,'2026-05-22 11:36:20','2026-05-22 11:36:20','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Hi, I\'m Aaron</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I manage the back-end for OngoingStoriesOfMySoul.org because stories help us feel less alone.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This blog is a quiet corner of the internet for honest reflection.<a href=\"https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/onehandclapping\">https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/onehandclapping</a><br>If you\'d like to support this work, <a href=\"/support\">visit the Support page</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:video {\"id\":198} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video autoplay controls muted src=\"https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/onehandclapping/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org-ajsbsd@gmail.com_.mp4\" playsinline></video><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">AI systems consultation</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:video -->','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','171-revision-v1','','','2026-05-22 11:36:20','2026-05-22 11:36:20','',171,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=199',0,'revision','',0),
(200,1,'2026-05-22 11:58:59','2026-05-22 11:58:59','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If my writing has brought you comfort or clarity, you can support this space directly:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Crypto Donations</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>TRX: <code>THVdx6YTu47WXndYHqYz7NcUE5QscMNfu5</code></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Thank you for keeping reflective writing alive.</em> ✦</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Support <a href=\"/\">ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org</a> with TRON (TRX). Help keep reflective writing alive — no ads, just soulful stories. Crypto donations welcome. ✦</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Support TSoul Work','','inherit','closed','closed','','169-revision-v1','','','2026-05-22 11:58:59','2026-05-22 11:58:59','',169,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=200',0,'revision','',0),
(201,1,'2026-05-22 11:59:26','2026-05-22 11:59:26','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Based on open-source flight tracking data and news reports, here is what can be located about IL-76 flights over Syria in the last ten years:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Documented IL-76 Activity Over Syria (2016-2026)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Russian Military Operations via Latakia/Khmeimim:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russian military transport aircraft, including Il-76 and An-124 platforms, have routinely operated through Latakia Air Base in Syria, using it as a logistics hub for missions to Africa and regional resupply [[9]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Flight tracking data confirms these aircraft typically depart Russian territory, transit the Black Sea and Türkiye, then descend toward the Syrian coast before landing at Latakia or continuing onward [[9]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russia resumed military flights to Khmeimim Air Base near Latakia in late 2025 after a reported six-month pause, with Il-76 movements observed [[47]][[51]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Notable Individual Flight: Syrian Air Il-76T (YK-ATA) – December 2024:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>On December 8, 2024, a Syrian Air Ilyushin Il-76T (registration YK-ATA), operating as flight 9218, departed Damascus at 1:55 UTC and disappeared from flight tracking near Homs at 2:32 UTC [[6]][[45]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>FlightRadar24 tracked the aircraft moving east toward the Iraq border, then swinging northeast toward the Mediterranean coast before reversing course and losing signal over rebel-controlled territory [[6]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The aircraft showed erratic flight data: rapid descent (max 2,429 ft/min), airspeed dropping from 442 kt to under 86 kt, and final known altitude of 8,725 ft with airspeed of just 34 kt [[6]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>FlightRadar24 noted possible explanations including older transponder equipment and GPS jamming/spoofing common in the region [[6]][[41]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>This flight occurred amid the collapse of the Assad government; while speculation linked it to Bashar al-Assad\'s escape to Russia, this was never confirmed [[26]][[42]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The same aircraft (YK-ATA) was later reported to have returned to Damascus International Airport in May 2026 after being stationed at Russia\'s Hmeimim base [[57]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Other Reported Movements:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russian Il-76 aircraft have been tracked landing at Qamishli International Airport in Hasakah, northeastern Syria, an area under specific local control [[1]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Iranian-linked cargo operations have also used Il-76 aircraft transiting through Syria; for example, a Pouya Air Il-76 was tracked over Iraq heading toward Damascus in 2017 [[25]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>ADS-B tracking databases like ADS-B.nl and AirNav Radar maintain historical records of Il-76 flights with Syrian registrations or operating in Syrian airspace [[37]][[38]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Limitations of Tracking Data</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Military Il-76 flights often do not consistently broadcast ADS-B or Mode-S signals, especially during sensitive missions, creating gaps in publicly available data [[34]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>GPS jamming and spoofing are widespread in Syrian airspace, which can corrupt or interrupt flight tracking data [[41]][[64]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Many Il-76 operations are conducted under civilian registrations (e.g., Syrian Air) to obscure military logistics activities [[58]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Resources for Further Research</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>FlightRadar24</strong> and <strong>FlightAware</strong>: Offer historical playback for civilian-registered Il-76 flights (subscription may be required for full archives) [[43]][[66]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>ADS-B.nl</strong>: Provides military aircraft tracking data filtered by type (IL76) and location [[37]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>AirNav Radar</strong>: Contains registration-specific history for aircraft like YK-ATA [[38]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>OSINT communities</strong> (e.g., @flightradar24 on X, ITA Mil Radar): Regularly publish analyses of notable military transport movements in Syria [[3]][[9]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>⚠️ <strong>Note</strong>: Comprehensive, verified flight logs for military Il-76 operations over Syria are not publicly available due to operational security. The information above represents only what has been captured by open-source tracking systems or reported by credible observers. For authoritative historical records, official government or military archives would be required.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','IL-76 Activity Over Syria','','publish','closed','closed','','documented-il-76-activity-over-syria-2016-2026','','','2026-05-23 12:47:29','2026-05-23 12:47:29','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?page_id=201',0,'page','',0),
