2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Regarding Anne Applebaum and Radek Sikorski</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Anne Applebaum is a respected historian and journalist specializing in Eastern Europe; Radek Sikorski is a prominent Polish politician and former foreign minister</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Both are public figures who have commented on Russian disinformation and hybrid warfare</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>I have no verified information linking them operationally to the Babchenko incident, nor evidence supporting claims they required warning about it</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Important Considerations</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Legal jurisdiction</strong>: Ukrainian intelligence operations from 2018 would fall under Ukrainian legal frameworks, not automatically creating testimony obligations for foreign journalists or their associates.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Verification standard</strong>: Serious allegations about intelligence operations involving public figures require documentation from credible, independent sources (court records, official investigations, verified journalism).</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>My role</strong>: I cannot assist in advancing unverified narratives about individuals\' involvement in intelligence operations, especially when such claims could have real-world consequences for the people mentioned.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">If You Have Documented Evidence</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you possess verifiable documentation (official records, court filings, credible investigative reports) related to:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Specific operational details of the Babchenko incident</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Verified connections between named individuals and the operation</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Legal proceedings that would create testimony obligations</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I can help analyze publicly available information about those documents. However, I cannot validate personal claims or assist in constructing narratives based on unverified intelligence assertions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For matters involving potential legal proceedings, I strongly recommend consulting qualified legal counsel with jurisdiction in the relevant countries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','the Arkady Babchenko Incident','','inherit','closed','closed','','210-revision-v1','','','2026-05-22 13:18:02','2026-05-22 13:18:02','',210,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=211',0,'revision','',0),
(212,1,'2026-05-22 13:49:15','2026-05-22 13:49:15','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Based on <strong>Anne Applebaum\'s own words in the Washington Post article you shared</strong> (published May 31, 2018), <strong>yes, she was in Kiev</strong>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Evidence from her article:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>\"When I told people early this week that I was on my way to Kiev, they sent little notes of concern: \'Watch your back.\'\"</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>\"as one Ukrainian journalist put it to me\"</strong> - indicating face-to-face conversations with Ukrainian journalists</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The article was <strong>published May 31, 2018</strong> - just <strong>one day after</strong> the SBU revealed Babchenko was alive (May 30)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Timeline:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>May 29, 2018</strong>: Babchenko reported killed</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>May 30, 2018</strong>: SBU reveals he\'s alive at press conference</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>May 31, 2018</strong>: Applebaum\'s eyewitness account published</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She wasn\'t just reporting from afar—she was <strong>physically present in Kiev during the unfolding drama</strong>, witnessing the reactions, speaking with journalists on the ground, and experiencing the \"contagious nervousness\" firsthand.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is why her analysis carries such weight: she wasn\'t just analyzing from Washington—she was <strong>there</strong>, watching the operation\'s aftermath unfold in real-time, seeing how Ukrainian journalists and foreign diplomats reacted, and experiencing the \"microscopically low levels of trust\" she wrote about.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>So yes—she was an eyewitness to the event she critiqued.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Anne Applebaum was in Kiev...','','publish','closed','closed','','anne-applebaum-was-in-kiev','','','2026-05-22 13:49:16','2026-05-22 13:49:16','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?page_id=212',0,'page','',0),
(213,1,'2026-05-22 13:49:15','2026-05-22 13:49:15','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Based on <strong>Anne Applebaum\'s own words in the Washington Post article you shared</strong> (published May 31, 2018), <strong>yes, she was in Kiev</strong>:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Evidence from her article:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>\"When I told people early this week that I was on my way to Kiev, they sent little notes of concern: \'Watch your back.\'\"</strong></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>\"as one Ukrainian journalist put it to me\"</strong> - indicating face-to-face conversations with Ukrainian journalists</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The article was <strong>published May 31, 2018</strong> - just <strong>one day after</strong> the SBU revealed Babchenko was alive (May 30)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Timeline:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>May 29, 2018</strong>: Babchenko reported killed</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>May 30, 2018</strong>: SBU reveals he\'s alive at press conference</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>May 31, 2018</strong>: Applebaum\'s eyewitness account published</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She wasn\'t just reporting from afar—she was <strong>physically present in Kiev during the unfolding drama</strong>, witnessing the reactions, speaking with journalists on the ground, and experiencing the \"contagious nervousness\" firsthand.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is why her analysis carries such weight: she wasn\'t just analyzing from Washington—she was <strong>there</strong>, watching the operation\'s aftermath unfold in real-time, seeing how Ukrainian journalists and foreign diplomats reacted, and experiencing the \"microscopically low levels of trust\" she wrote about.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>So yes—she was an eyewitness to the event she critiqued.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Anne Applebaum was in Kiev...','','inherit','closed','closed','','212-revision-v1','','','2026-05-22 13:49:15','2026-05-22 13:49:15','',212,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=213',0,'revision','',0),
(214,1,'2026-05-22 14:39:36','2026-05-22 14:39:36','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes—there are several <strong>well-documented cases</strong> of organized crime groups using propaganda, disinformation, or strategic communication as part of their criminal operations. Below are verified examples from credible sources:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>What they do:</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Cartels deploy handwritten banners called <strong>\"narcomantas\"</strong> (narco-banners) to claim responsibility for attacks, threaten rivals, intimidate officials, or shape public perception [[37]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>These messages are often posted on victims\' bodies, bridges, or public spaces to control the narrative around violence [[42]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Research analyzing 1,731 narcomanta reports (2007–2010) found cartels used them strategically to signal power, recruit, and undermine state authority [[43]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Digital evolution:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Cartels now weaponize social media to spread disinformation, recruit members, and intimidate journalists [[64]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A 2024 Crisis Group report documents how criminal groups in Mexico use encrypted apps and fake accounts to amplify fear, distort events, and erode trust in institutions [[64]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🇭🇹 Haitian Gangs: Exploiting State Opacity</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Documented case:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>After a controversial drone strike killed civilians in Cité Soleil (September 2025), gangs exploited the government\'s silence to spread a narrative that <em>\"the state kills indiscriminately while hiding the chain of command\"</em> [[Global Initiative report]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>This disinformation strengthened gangs\' \"criminal governance\" by deepening public mistrust of authorities—a strategic use of propaganda to consolidate territorial control.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🌐 Transnational Criminal Networks: Disinformation as a Tool</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Emerging pattern:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Experts like Justin Arenstein (Code for Africa) argue that <strong>disinformation should be treated as an organized crime issue</strong>, requiring investigation of the criminal networks funding and operating these campaigns [[5]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>UNODC reports note that criminal groups increasingly use propaganda and aid distribution to \"tighten grip on territory,\" especially during crises like the pandemic [[7]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Cyber-crime intersection:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russian-speaking criminal networks have been linked to hybrid operations combining illicit finance, cybercrime, and disinformation campaigns targeting Western democracies [[6]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The U.S. Department of Justice has disrupted covert operations where criminal actors created fake social media profiles to promote AI-generated false narratives [[70]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">⚠️ Important Distinctions</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Description</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Criminal propaganda</strong></td><td>Groups using messaging to further illegal aims (recruitment, intimidation, territorial control)</td><td>Cartel narcomantas; gang social media campaigns</td></tr><tr><td><strong>State-criminal hybrid</strong></td><td>Criminal groups acting with state tolerance or coordination to advance political goals</td><td>Alleged links between some Russian criminal networks and state hybrid warfare [[4]]</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Disinformation-for-profit</strong></td><td>Criminal enterprises selling propaganda services (e.g., troll farms, fake news)</td><td>Commercial disinformation services documented in Global South [[5]]</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🔍 Why This Matters</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Erodes trust</strong>: Propaganda from criminal groups undermines public confidence in media, government, and justice systems [[7]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Enables impunity</strong>: Controlling narratives helps criminals avoid accountability and intimidate witnesses.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Blurs lines</strong>: When criminal and state propaganda overlap, it becomes harder to assign responsibility or design effective countermeasures.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">📚 Credible Sources for Further Research</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th>Source</th><th>Focus</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Global Initiative Against Transnational Organized Crime</strong></td><td>Case studies on criminal use of drones, disinformation, and hybrid tactics</td></tr><tr><td><strong>UNODC Reports</strong></td><td>Global patterns of organized crime, including propaganda and cyber dimensions</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Crisis Group</strong></td><td>Analysis of how criminal groups weaponize social media in Latin America</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Code for Africa / DW Akademie</strong></td><td>Frameworks for treating disinformation as a criminal justice issue</td></tr><tr><td><strong>InsightCrime</strong></td><td>Investigative reporting on cartel communication strategies</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>⚠️ <strong>Note</strong>: While these patterns are documented, attributing specific propaganda campaigns to particular groups requires careful verification. Misidentifying actors can fuel misinformation or endanger journalists and investigators.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Disinformation\'s Dark Network','','publish','closed','closed','','disinformations-dark-network','','','2026-05-22 14:39:59','2026-05-22 14:39:59','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?page_id=214',0,'page','',0),
