(218,1,'2026-05-22 14:57:40','2026-05-22 14:57:40','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thank you for sharing this. You\'re referring to the <strong>November 25-26, 2018 Kerch Strait incident</strong>. Let me provide accurate context:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Happened:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>November 25, 2018:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Three Ukrainian naval vessels (two gunboats and a tugboat) attempted to transit from the Black Sea through the Kerch Strait into the Sea of Azov</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russian forces <strong>seized all three vessels</strong> and detained 24 Ukrainian sailors</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russia claimed Ukraine failed to properly notify them and violated territorial waters</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>November 26, 2018:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russian Su-25 attack aircraft patrolled over the Crimean Bridge</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>This was documented in the video you found, filmed by witnesses near the bridge</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russia temporarily closed the Kerch Strait to shipping</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Key Context:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>The Su-25 \"Grach\"</strong> is a Soviet-designed ground-attack aircraft - not typically a maritime patrol platform, making its presence notable</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Strategic significance</strong>: This occurred after Russia\'s 2014 annexation of Crimea and construction of the Crimean Bridge (opened May 2018)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>International response</strong>: The incident led to:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Ukraine declaring martial law</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>UN General Assembly resolution condemning Russia</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>International Tribunal for the Law of the Sea ordering Russia to release the vessels (which it eventually did in September 2019)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You were right to point me to this specific incident. The Su-25 patrol over the bridge was a visible show of force during a major Russia-Ukraine confrontation. Is there a specific aspect of this incident you\'d like to explore further?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Su-25 Grach is a Soviet-designed...','','publish','closed','closed','','november-2018-kerch-strait','','','2026-05-23 12:47:13','2026-05-23 12:47:13','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?page_id=218',0,'page','',0),
(219,1,'2026-05-22 14:57:40','2026-05-22 14:57:40','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thank you for sharing this. You\'re referring to the <strong>November 25-26, 2018 Kerch Strait incident</strong>. Let me provide accurate context:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Happened:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>November 25, 2018:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Three Ukrainian naval vessels (two gunboats and a tugboat) attempted to transit from the Black Sea through the Kerch Strait into the Sea of Azov</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russian forces <strong>seized all three vessels</strong> and detained 24 Ukrainian sailors</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russia claimed Ukraine failed to properly notify them and violated territorial waters</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>November 26, 2018:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russian Su-25 attack aircraft patrolled over the Crimean Bridge</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>This was documented in the video you found, filmed by witnesses near the bridge</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russia temporarily closed the Kerch Strait to shipping</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Key Context:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>The Su-25 \"Grach\"</strong> is a Soviet-designed ground-attack aircraft - not typically a maritime patrol platform, making its presence notable</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Strategic significance</strong>: This occurred after Russia\'s 2014 annexation of Crimea and construction of the Crimean Bridge (opened May 2018)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>International response</strong>: The incident led to:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Ukraine declaring martial law</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>UN General Assembly resolution condemning Russia</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>International Tribunal for the Law of the Sea ordering Russia to release the vessels (which it eventually did in September 2019)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You were right to point me to this specific incident. The Su-25 patrol over the bridge was a visible show of force during a major Russia-Ukraine confrontation. Is there a specific aspect of this incident you\'d like to explore further?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','November 2018 Kerch Strait','','inherit','closed','closed','','218-revision-v1','','','2026-05-22 14:57:40','2026-05-22 14:57:40','',218,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=219',0,'revision','',0),
(220,1,'2026-05-22 15:07:00','2026-05-22 15:07:00','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thank you for sharing this. You\'re referring to the <strong>November 25-26, 2018 Kerch Strait incident</strong>. Let me provide accurate context:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Happened:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>November 25, 2018:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Three Ukrainian naval vessels (two gunboats and a tugboat) attempted to transit from the Black Sea through the Kerch Strait into the Sea of Azov</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russian forces <strong>seized all three vessels</strong> and detained 24 Ukrainian sailors</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russia claimed Ukraine failed to properly notify them and violated territorial waters</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>November 26, 2018:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russian Su-25 attack aircraft patrolled over the Crimean Bridge</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>This was documented in the video you found, filmed by witnesses near the bridge</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russia temporarily closed the Kerch Strait to shipping</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Key Context:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>The Su-25 \"Grach\"</strong> is a Soviet-designed ground-attack aircraft - not typically a maritime patrol platform, making its presence notable</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Strategic significance</strong>: This occurred after Russia\'s 2014 annexation of Crimea and construction of the Crimean Bridge (opened May 2018)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>International response</strong>: The incident led to:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Ukraine declaring martial law</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>UN General Assembly resolution condemning Russia</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>International Tribunal for the Law of the Sea ordering Russia to release the vessels (which it eventually did in September 2019)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You were right to point me to this specific incident. The Su-25 patrol over the bridge was a visible show of force during a major Russia-Ukraine confrontation. Is there a specific aspect of this incident you\'d like to explore further?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Su-25 \"Grach\" is a Soviet-designed ground-attack aircraft...','','inherit','closed','closed','','218-revision-v1','','','2026-05-22 15:07:00','2026-05-22 15:07:00','',218,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=220',0,'revision','',0),
