(222,1,'2026-05-22 15:37:19','2026-05-22 15:37:19','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>🌍 On Applebaum as a \"Globetrotter\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes. That makes complete sense.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When a journalist like Anne Applebaum continues to publish clear-eyed, bylined work—whether about Zuzana Čaputová\'s historic 2019 election in Slovakia, democratic resilience in Eastern Europe, or the mechanics of disinformation—it signals something powerful:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>✅ <strong>She is still writing</strong> → She is still free<br>✅ <strong>She is still traveling</strong> → She is still able to move<br>✅ <strong>She is still analyzing</strong> → She is still thinking critically</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That\'s not just journalism. It\'s a quiet form of reassurance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🌍 On Applebaum as a \"Globetrotter\"</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You\'re right—her bylines span:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Washington Post</strong> (her long-time column)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>The Atlantic</strong> (where she\'s a staff writer)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Books and lectures</strong> across Europe and North America</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>On-the-ground reporting</strong> from Kyiv, Warsaw, Vilnius, and beyond</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Her work doesn\'t just <em>describe</em> democratic struggles—it embodies the mobility, access, and intellectual freedom that authoritarian systems seek to restrict.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">📰 Why Reading Her Felt Like Safety</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There\'s a psychological anchor in seeing a trusted voice continue to speak clearly amid chaos. When the Babchenko operation blurred truth and performance, returning to Applebaum\'s structured, sourced, reflective prose was a way to re-ground:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>The world is complicated, but someone is still making sense of it.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That\'s not naive. It\'s human.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🤝 Final Thought</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You paid attention. You worried. You looked for signals. And when you saw her writing about Čaputová\'s victory—a story about hope, rule of law, and peaceful democratic transition—you felt a measure of relief.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That\'s not just about Applebaum. It\'s about why journalism matters: not just to inform, but to reassure, to connect, to say: <em>I am here. The work continues.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you ever want to revisit any of those articles, trace her reporting timeline, or simply reflect on that period—I\'m here. No rush. No agenda. Just space to think.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','✅ She is still writing →','','publish','open','open','','%e2%9c%85-she-is-still-writing-%e2%86%92','','','2026-05-22 15:37:20','2026-05-22 15:37:20','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=222',0,'post','',0),
(223,1,'2026-05-22 15:37:19','2026-05-22 15:37:19','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>🌍 On Applebaum as a \"Globetrotter\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes. That makes complete sense.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When a journalist like Anne Applebaum continues to publish clear-eyed, bylined work—whether about Zuzana Čaputová\'s historic 2019 election in Slovakia, democratic resilience in Eastern Europe, or the mechanics of disinformation—it signals something powerful:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>✅ <strong>She is still writing</strong> → She is still free<br>✅ <strong>She is still traveling</strong> → She is still able to move<br>✅ <strong>She is still analyzing</strong> → She is still thinking critically</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That\'s not just journalism. It\'s a quiet form of reassurance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🌍 On Applebaum as a \"Globetrotter\"</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You\'re right—her bylines span:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Washington Post</strong> (her long-time column)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>The Atlantic</strong> (where she\'s a staff writer)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Books and lectures</strong> across Europe and North America</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>On-the-ground reporting</strong> from Kyiv, Warsaw, Vilnius, and beyond</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Her work doesn\'t just <em>describe</em> democratic struggles—it embodies the mobility, access, and intellectual freedom that authoritarian systems seek to restrict.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">📰 Why Reading Her Felt Like Safety</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There\'s a psychological anchor in seeing a trusted voice continue to speak clearly amid chaos. When the Babchenko operation blurred truth and performance, returning to Applebaum\'s structured, sourced, reflective prose was a way to re-ground:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>The world is complicated, but someone is still making sense of it.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That\'s not naive. It\'s human.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🤝 Final Thought</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You paid attention. You worried. You looked for signals. And when you saw her writing about Čaputová\'s victory—a story about hope, rule of law, and peaceful democratic transition—you felt a measure of relief.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That\'s not just about Applebaum. It\'s about why journalism matters: not just to inform, but to reassure, to connect, to say: <em>I am here. The work continues.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you ever want to revisit any of those articles, trace her reporting timeline, or simply reflect on that period—I\'m here. No rush. No agenda. Just space to think.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','✅ She is still writing →','','inherit','closed','closed','','222-revision-v1','','','2026-05-22 15:37:19','2026-05-22 15:37:19','',222,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=223',0,'revision','',0),
(224,1,'2026-05-22 15:47:08','2026-05-22 15:47:08','{\n    \"show_on_front\": {\n        \"value\": \"page\",\n        \"type\": \"option\",\n        \"user_id\": 1,\n        \"date_modified_gmt\": \"2026-05-22 15:47:08\"\n    },\n    \"page_on_front\": {\n        \"value\": \"205\",\n        \"type\": \"option\",\n        \"user_id\": 1,\n        \"date_modified_gmt\": \"2026-05-22 15:47:08\"\n    },\n    \"page_for_posts\": {\n        \"value\": \"218\",\n        \"type\": \"option\",\n        \"user_id\": 1,\n        \"date_modified_gmt\": \"2026-05-22 15:47:08\"\n    }\n}','','','trash','closed','closed','','6664175a-2680-4fd0-9a43-72231be8bf25','','','2026-05-22 15:47:08','2026-05-22 15:47:08','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/2026/05/22/6664175a-2680-4fd0-9a43-72231be8bf25/',0,'customize_changeset','',0),
