(233,1,'2026-05-23 01:23:06','2026-05-23 01:23:06','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To overlay your website URL as a text watermark while keeping the video looping and syncing perfectly to the audio, you can use FFmpeg\'s <code>drawtext</code> filter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Because we are adding a video filter, the video has to be re-encoded anyway, which fits perfectly with the command we just built to handle the audio length constraint.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here is the updated command:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bash</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>ffmpeg -stream_loop -1 -i e92600d4-d884-4503-8f0f-4c8be4e8808b.mp4 -i \"10 - The RZA - RZA\'s Theme.wav\" -map 0:v -map 1:a -vf \"drawtext=text=\'OngoingStoriesOfMySoul.org\':x=w-tw-20:y=h-th-20:fontsize=24:fontcolor=white@0.6:box=1:boxcolor=black@0.4:boxborderw=10\" -c:v libx264 -crf 23 -pix_fmt yuv420p -c:a aac -shortest output.mp4\n</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Adjusting the Watermark Settings</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Inside the <code>-vf</code> (video filter) quotes, you can easily customize how the watermark looks and where it sits:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Position (<code>x=w-tw-20:y=h-th-20</code>)</strong>: This places the text in the <strong>bottom-right corner</strong> with a 20-pixel margin.<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><em>Top-Left:</em> Change to <code>x=20:y=20</code></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><em>Center:</em> Change to <code>x=(w-tw)/2:y=(h-th)/2</code></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Font Size (<code>fontsize=24</code>)</strong>: Change this number to make the text larger or smaller depending on your video\'s resolution.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Opacity (<code>fontcolor=white@0.6</code>)</strong>: The <code>@0.6</code> makes the white text 60% opaque (slightly translucent) so it doesn\'t distract too much from the video.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Background Box (<code>box=1:boxcolor=black@0.4</code>)</strong>: This places a subtle, semi-transparent black rectangle behind the text so it remains readable even if the video background turns pure white. If you don\'t want a background box, just delete <code>box=1:boxcolor=black@0.4:boxborderw=10</code>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Note on Fonts:</strong> If the command throws a font error, it means FFmpeg can\'t find your system\'s default font. You can fix this by adding a specific font path to the filter, like this: <code>fontfile=/Windows/Fonts/arial.ttf</code> (Windows) or <code>fontfile=/Library/Fonts/Arial.ttf</code> (Mac) right before the <code>text=</code> parameter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->','ffmpeg notes','','publish','closed','closed','','ffmpeg-notes','','','2026-05-23 01:23:06','2026-05-23 01:23:06','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?page_id=233',0,'page','',0),
