trong> (not $500) to sustain a real fight.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Urges Big Three workers to honor picket lines—building <strong>sector-wide leverage</strong>.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🧭 Political Orientation</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><tbody><tr><td>Element</td><td>WSWS Position</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Union bureaucracy</strong></td><td>A layer integrated into management; obstacle to struggle</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Democratic Party</strong></td><td>Instrument of capital; workers need independent political organization</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Strategy</strong></td><td>Rank-and-file committees → strike action → broader class confrontation</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Goal</strong></td><td>Socialist transformation: workers\' control of production and society</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🔗 Broader Context (Per WSWS)</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This fight is linked to:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>🚗 Contract battles at American Axle, Dana, Magna, Bridgewater</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>🏭 Rank-and-file slates at Ford Rouge, CNH Industrial</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>🎓 Student/academic worker strikes (Harvard, UMass Boston)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>🌍 Global inflation, war, and capitalist crisis</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The publication sees Lehman\'s campaign as part of a <strong>renewed international workers\' movement</strong> challenging both corporate power and the traditional labor leadership that accommodates it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">⚠️ Critical Note</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The WSWS represents the <strong>Socialist Equality Party (Fourth International)</strong>, a Trotskyist organization. Its analysis is explicitly revolutionary socialist: it does not seek to \"reform\" the UAW or capitalism, but to build independent working-class power aimed at overthrowing the capitalist system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Readers seeking alternative perspectives may also consult coverage from:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Mainstream labor media (<em>Labor Notes</em>, <em>In These Times</em>)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Business press (<em>Reuters</em>, <em>Bloomberg</em>)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Other leftist outlets (<em>Jacobin</em>, <em>Dissent</em>)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Want help finding primary sources, union statements, or contrasting analyses on the Nexteer struggle? I can assist with that.</em> 🛠️</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','📰 WSWS Perspective','','inherit','closed','closed','','241-revision-v1','','','2026-05-23 11:32:16','2026-05-23 11:32:16','',241,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=242',0,'revision','',0),
(243,1,'2026-05-23 12:47:13','2026-05-23 12:47:13','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thank you for sharing this. You\'re referring to the <strong>November 25-26, 2018 Kerch Strait incident</strong>. Let me provide accurate context:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What Happened:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>November 25, 2018:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Three Ukrainian naval vessels (two gunboats and a tugboat) attempted to transit from the Black Sea through the Kerch Strait into the Sea of Azov</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russian forces <strong>seized all three vessels</strong> and detained 24 Ukrainian sailors</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russia claimed Ukraine failed to properly notify them and violated territorial waters</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>November 26, 2018:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russian Su-25 attack aircraft patrolled over the Crimean Bridge</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>This was documented in the video you found, filmed by witnesses near the bridge</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russia temporarily closed the Kerch Strait to shipping</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Key Context:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>The Su-25 \"Grach\"</strong> is a Soviet-designed ground-attack aircraft - not typically a maritime patrol platform, making its presence notable</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Strategic significance</strong>: This occurred after Russia\'s 2014 annexation of Crimea and construction of the Crimean Bridge (opened May 2018)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>International response</strong>: The incident led to:</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Ukraine declaring martial law</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>UN General Assembly resolution condemning Russia</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>International Tribunal for the Law of the Sea ordering Russia to release the vessels (which it eventually did in September 2019)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You were right to point me to this specific incident. The Su-25 patrol over the bridge was a visible show of force during a major Russia-Ukraine confrontation. Is there a specific aspect of this incident you\'d like to explore further?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Su-25 Grach is a Soviet-designed...','','inherit','closed','closed','','218-revision-v1','','','2026-05-23 12:47:13','2026-05-23 12:47:13','',218,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=243',0,'revision','',0),
(244,1,'2026-05-23 12:47:29','2026-05-23 12:47:29','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Based on open-source flight tracking data and news reports, here is what can be located about IL-76 flights over Syria in the last ten years:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Documented IL-76 Activity Over Syria (2016-2026)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Russian Military Operations via Latakia/Khmeimim:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russian military transport aircraft, including Il-76 and An-124 platforms, have routinely operated through Latakia Air Base in Syria, using it as a logistics hub for missions to Africa and regional resupply [[9]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Flight tracking data confirms these aircraft typically depart Russian territory, transit the Black Sea and Türkiye, then descend toward the Syrian coast before landing at Latakia or continuing onward [[9]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russia resumed military flights to Khmeimim Air Base near Latakia in late 2025 after a reported six-month pause, with Il-76 movements observed [[47]][[51]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Notable Individual Flight: Syrian Air Il-76T (YK-ATA) – December 2024:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>On December 8, 2024, a Syrian Air Ilyushin Il-76T (registration YK-ATA), operating as flight 9218, departed Damascus at 1:55 UTC and disappeared from flight tracking near Homs at 2:32 UTC [[6]][[45]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>FlightRadar24 tracked the aircraft moving east toward the Iraq border, then swinging northeast toward the Mediterranean coast before reversing course and losing signal over rebel-controlled territory [[6]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The aircraft showed erratic flight data: rapid descent (max 2,429 ft/min), airspeed dropping from 442 kt to under 86 kt, and final known altitude of 8,725 ft with airspeed of just 34 kt [[6]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>FlightRadar24 noted possible explanations including older transponder equipment and GPS jamming/spoofing common in the region [[6]][[41]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>This flight occurred amid the collapse of the Assad government; while speculation linked it to Bashar al-Assad\'s escape to Russia, this was never confirmed [[26]][[42]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The same aircraft (YK-ATA) was later reported to have returned to Damascus International Airport in May 2026 after being stationed at Russia\'s Hmeimim base [[57]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Other Reported Movements:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Russian Il-76 aircraft have been tracked landing at Qamishli International Airport in Hasakah, northeastern Syria, an area under specific local control [[1]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Iranian-linked cargo operations have also used Il-76 aircraft transiting through Syria; for example, a Pouya Air Il-76 was tracked over Iraq heading toward Damascus in 2017 [[25]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>ADS-B tracking databases like ADS-B.nl and AirNav Radar maintain historical records of Il-76 flights with Syrian registrations or operating in Syrian airspace [[37]][[38]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Limitations of Tracking Data</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Military Il-76 flights often do not consistently broadcast ADS-B or Mode-S signals, especially during sensitive missions, creating gaps in publicly available data [[34]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>GPS jamming and spoofing are widespread in Syrian airspace, which can corrupt or interrupt flight tracking data [[41]][[64]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Many Il-76 operations are conducted under civilian registrations (e.g., Syrian Air) to obscure military logistics activities [[58]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Resources for Further Research</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>FlightRadar24</strong> and <strong>FlightAware</strong>: Offer historical playback for civilian-registered Il-76 flights (subscription may be required for full archives) [[43]][[66]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>ADS-B.nl</strong>: Provides military aircraft tracking data filtered by type (IL76) and location [[37]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>AirNav Radar</strong>: Contains registration-specific history for aircraft like YK-ATA [[38]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>OSINT communities</strong> (e.g., @flightradar24 on X, ITA Mil Radar): Regularly publish analyses of notable military transport movements in Syria [[3]][[9]].</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>⚠️ <strong>Note</strong>: Comprehensive, verified flight logs for military Il-76 operations over Syria are not publicly available due to operational security. The information above represents only what has been captured by open-source tracking systems or reported by credible observers. For authoritative historical records, official government or military archives would be required.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','IL-76 Activity Over Syria','','inherit','closed','closed','','201-revision-v1','','','2026-05-23 12:47:29','2026-05-23 12:47:29','',201,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=244',0,'revision','',0),
(246,1,'2026-05-23 12:49:54','2026-05-23 12:49:54','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Example Prompts &amp; Prompting Guide</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Google\'s Veo 3.1 is a state-of-the-art video generation model available via Vertex AI and Gemini, designed for professional-grade creative control with synchronized audio, improved prompt adherence, and advanced features like \"first/last frame\" transitions and \"ingredients to video\" consistency [[2]][[6]].</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🔑 The 5-Element Prompt Formula</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For best results, structure prompts using this framework:<br><strong>[Cinematography] + [Subject] + [Action] + [Context] + [Style &amp; Ambiance]</strong> [[6]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Cinematography</strong>: Camera angle, movement, lens (e.g., \"close-up,\" \"slow dolly in,\" \"shallow depth of field\")</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Subject</strong>: Who or what is the focus (be specific: \"a woman in her 30s with curly auburn hair\")</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Action</strong>: What they\'re doing (e.g., \"whispering urgently,\" \"running through falling leaves\")</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Context</strong>: Setting and environment (e.g., \"rainy Tokyo alley at night, neon signs reflecting on wet pavement\")</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Style &amp; Ambiance</strong>: Visual tone, lighting, mood (e.g., \"film noir aesthetic, high-contrast black and white, dramatic shadows\")</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🎯 Ready-to-Use Example Prompts</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🎥 Cinematic Portrait</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"Close-up with shallow depth of field, a young woman looking out a bus window at passing city lights, her reflection faintly visible on the glass. Inside a bus at night during a rainstorm. Melancholic mood with cool blue tones, cinematic lighting. Ambient sound: gentle rain tapping on windows, distant city traffic.\"</em> [[6]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🌌 Fantasy Scene</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"Wide drone shot ascending slowly, a lone explorer in a weathered leather coat standing at the edge of a floating island covered in glowing crystal trees. Mist swirls below, twin moons rise in a violet sky. Epic fantasy style, soft volumetric lighting. SFX: ethereal wind chimes, distant orchestral swell.\"</em> [[7]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🕵️ Noir Dialogue Scene <em>(using Ingredients to Video)</em></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"Medium shot, film noir style. A detective in a trench coat sits behind a cluttered desk, cigarette smoke curling in a shaft of light from a venetian blind. He looks up and says in a weary voice: \'Of all the offices in this town, you had to walk into mine.\' Ambient: distant jazz piano, rain on windowpane.\"</em> [[6]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🏁 Action Sequence <em>(Timestamp Prompting)</em></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"[00:00-00:02] Low-angle tracking shot: muddy off-road buggy splashes through a shallow river, water exploding upward. [00:02-00:04] Cut to POV from inside the buggy: windshield wipers struggle against mud spray. [00:04-00:06] Wide shot: second truck bursts through the water curtain behind it. SFX: roaring engines, splashing water, tire crunch on gravel.\"</em> [[6]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🎄 Lifestyle / Social Content</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"Overhead shot, cozy cafe morning. Hands pouring latte art into a ceramic cup, steam rising. Sunlight streams through a window with hanging plants. Warm, inviting aesthetic, soft natural lighting. Ambient: gentle espresso machine hiss, soft acoustic guitar.\"</em> [[3]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🎭 Stop-Motion Humor</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"Stop-motion animation style. A tiny camper in a tent whispers: \'I\'m one with nature now!\' A friendly bear peeks from behind a tree and replies: \'Nature would prefer some personal space.\' Playful tone, soft clay textures, warm sunset lighting.\"</em> [[7]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🔊 Audio Prompting Tips</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Veo 3.1 generates synchronized audio—include these elements explicitly [[6]][[7]]:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Dialogue</strong>: Use quotes → <em>She says, \"We need to leave now.\"</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Sound Effects</strong>: Label clearly → <em>SFX: thunder cracks, glass shatters</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Ambience</strong>: Set the scene → <em>Ambient: forest birdsong, distant waterfall</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Music Style</strong>: Guide the mood → <em>Background: soft piano melody, hopeful tone</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🛠️ Advanced Workflows</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">✦ First &amp; Last Frame Transition</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Generate start/end images with Gemini Flash Image</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Input both into Veo 3.1 with a prompt describing the motion and audio</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Example: <em>\"Smooth 180-degree arc shot circling a singer on stage, transitioning from front view to crowd POV. She sings: \'When you look me in the eyes…\' Crowd cheers swell.\"</em> [[6]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">✦ Ingredients to Video (Consistency)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Upload reference images of characters, objects, or styles, then prompt:<br><em>\"Using the provided images of the detective, the woman, and the office, create a medium shot where the detective says…\"</em> [[6]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">✦ Timestamp Prompting for Multi-Shot Scenes</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Break an 8-second clip into timed segments for precise pacing:<br><em>\"[00:00-00:03] … [00:03-00:06] … [00:06-00:08] …\"</em> [[6]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">⚠️ Common Pitfalls to Avoid</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>❌ Vague language: <em>\"cool video,\" \"nice scene\"</em> → Use specific, sensory details</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>❌ Overloading prompts: Too many actions/objects → Focus on one clear moment</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>❌ Ignoring audio: Veo 3.1\'s sync is a key strength—always describe sound</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>❌ Cross-platform watermarks: Upload native, watermark-free files for best quality [[38]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">💡 Pro Tips</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Use <strong>negative prompts</strong> to exclude elements: <em>\"a forest path with no buildings or roads\"</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Enhance simple ideas with <strong>Gemini</strong>: Ask it to expand your prompt with cinematic language</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Start short: Test 4-second clips before committing to 8-second generations</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>For social content: Prioritize strong first-frame hooks and vertical (9:16) framing [[18]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Veo 3.1 rewards specificity, cinematic thinking, and audio-aware prompting. Whether you\'re crafting a product ad, short film, or social reel, structured prompts unlock its full creative potential. For enterprise use, access Veo 3.1 via <strong>Vertex AI</strong>; for experimentation, try it in <strong>Gemini Advanced</strong> or <strong>Google Flow</strong> [[2]][[6]].</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Need help adapting a prompt for your specific use case? Just ask! 🎥✨</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','🎬 Veo 3.1','','publish','closed','closed','','%f0%9f%8e%ac-veo-3-1','','','2026-05-23 12:49:54','2026-05-23 12:49:54','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?page_id=246',0,'page','',0),
(247,1,'2026-05-23 12:49:54','2026-05-23 12:49:54','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":1} -->\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Example Prompts &amp; Prompting Guide</h1>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Google\'s Veo 3.1 is a state-of-the-art video generation model available via Vertex AI and Gemini, designed for professional-grade creative control with synchronized audio, improved prompt adherence, and advanced features like \"first/last frame\" transitions and \"ingredients to video\" consistency [[2]][[6]].</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🔑 The 5-Element Prompt Formula</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For best results, structure prompts using this framework:<br><strong>[Cinematography] + [Subject] + [Action] + [Context] + [Style &amp; Ambiance]</strong> [[6]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Cinematography</strong>: Camera angle, movement, lens (e.g., \"close-up,\" \"slow dolly in,\" \"shallow depth of field\")</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Subject</strong>: Who or what is the focus (be specific: \"a woman in her 30s with curly auburn hair\")</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Action</strong>: What they\'re doing (e.g., \"whispering urgently,\" \"running through falling leaves\")</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Context</strong>: Setting and environment (e.g., \"rainy Tokyo alley at night, neon signs reflecting on wet pavement\")</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Style &amp; Ambiance</strong>: Visual tone, lighting, mood (e.g., \"film noir aesthetic, high-contrast black and white, dramatic shadows\")</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🎯 Ready-to-Use Example Prompts</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🎥 Cinematic Portrait</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"Close-up with shallow depth of field, a young woman looking out a bus window at passing city lights, her reflection faintly visible on the glass. Inside a bus at night during a rainstorm. Melancholic mood with cool blue tones, cinematic lighting. Ambient sound: gentle rain tapping on windows, distant city traffic.\"</em> [[6]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🌌 Fantasy Scene</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"Wide drone shot ascending slowly, a lone explorer in a weathered leather coat standing at the edge of a floating island covered in glowing crystal trees. Mist swirls below, twin moons rise in a violet sky. Epic fantasy style, soft volumetric lighting. SFX: ethereal wind chimes, distant orchestral swell.\"</em> [[7]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🕵️ Noir Dialogue Scene <em>(using Ingredients to Video)</em></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"Medium shot, film noir style. A detective in a trench coat sits behind a cluttered desk, cigarette smoke curling in a shaft of light from a venetian blind. He looks up and says in a weary voice: \'Of all the offices in this town, you had to walk into mine.\' Ambient: distant jazz piano, rain on windowpane.\"</em> [[6]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🏁 Action Sequence <em>(Timestamp Prompting)</em></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"[00:00-00:02] Low-angle tracking shot: muddy off-road buggy splashes through a shallow river, water exploding upward. [00:02-00:04] Cut to POV from inside the buggy: windshield wipers struggle against mud spray. [00:04-00:06] Wide shot: second truck bursts through the water curtain behind it. SFX: roaring engines, splashing water, tire crunch on gravel.\"</em> [[6]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🎄 Lifestyle / Social Content</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"Overhead shot, cozy cafe morning. Hands pouring latte art into a ceramic cup, steam rising. Sunlight streams through a window with hanging plants. Warm, inviting aesthetic, soft natural lighting. Ambient: gentle espresso machine hiss, soft acoustic guitar.\"</em> [[3]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🎭 Stop-Motion Humor</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>\"Stop-motion animation style. A tiny camper in a tent whispers: \'I\'m one with nature now!\' A friendly bear peeks from behind a tree and replies: \'Nature would prefer some personal space.\' Playful tone, soft clay textures, warm sunset lighting.\"</em> [[7]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🔊 Audio Prompting Tips</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Veo 3.1 generates synchronized audio—include these elements explicitly [[6]][[7]]:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Dialogue</strong>: Use quotes → <em>She says, \"We need to leave now.\"</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Sound Effects</strong>: Label clearly → <em>SFX: thunder cracks, glass shatters</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Ambience</strong>: Set the scene → <em>Ambient: forest birdsong, distant waterfall</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Music Style</strong>: Guide the mood → <em>Background: soft piano melody, hopeful tone</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">🛠️ Advanced Workflows</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">✦ First &amp; Last Frame Transition</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Generate start/end images with Gemini Flash Image</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Input both into Veo 3.1 with a prompt describing the motion and audio</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Example: <em>\"Smooth 180-degree arc shot circling a singer on stage, transitioning from front view to crowd POV. She sings: \'When you look me in the eyes…\' Crowd cheers swell.\"</em> [[6]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">✦ Ingredients to Video (Consistency)</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Upload reference images of characters, objects, or styles, then prompt:<br><em>\"Using the provided images of the detective, the woman, and the office, create a medium shot where the detective says…\"</em> [[6]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">✦ Timestamp Prompting for Multi-Shot Scenes</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Break an 8-second clip into timed segments for precise pacing:<br><em>\"[00:00-00:03] … [00:03-00:06] … [00:06-00:08] …\"</em> [[6]]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">⚠️ Common Pitfalls to Avoid</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>❌ Vague language: <em>\"cool video,\" \"nice scene\"</em> → Use specific, sensory details</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>❌ Overloading prompts: Too many actions/objects → Focus on one clear moment</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>❌ Ignoring audio: Veo 3.1\'s sync is a key strength—always describe sound</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>❌ Cross-platform watermarks: Upload native, watermark-free files for best quality [[38]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">💡 Pro Tips</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Use <strong>negative prompts</strong> to exclude elements: <em>\"a forest path with no buildings or roads\"</em></li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Enhance simple ideas with <strong>Gemini</strong>: Ask it to expand your prompt with cinematic language</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Start short: Test 4-second clips before committing to 8-second generations</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>For social content: Prioritize strong first-frame hooks and vertical (9:16) framing [[18]]</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Veo 3.1 rewards specificity, cinematic thinking, and audio-aware prompting. Whether you\'re crafting a product ad, short film, or social reel, structured prompts unlock its full creative potential. For enterprise use, access Veo 3.1 via <strong>Vertex AI</strong>; for experimentation, try it in <strong>Gemini Advanced</strong> or <strong>Google Flow</strong> [[2]][[6]].</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Need help adapting a prompt for your specific use case? Just ask! 🎥✨</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','🎬 Veo 3.1','','inherit','closed','closed','','246-revision-v1','','','2026-05-23 12:49:54','2026-05-23 12:49:54','',246,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/?p=247',0,'revision','',0),
(248,1,'2026-05-23 14:14:29','2026-05-23 14:14:29','<!-- wp:image {\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://img5tv.cdnvideo.ru/webp/shared/files/202605/1_2578559.jpg\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Вооруженные силы России нанесли удар по предприятию военно-промышленного комплекса Украины, объектам энергетики, используемым в интересах ВСУ, а также по цехам сборки и местам хранения беспилотников дальнего действия. Об этом 23 мая сообщило Минобороны РФ.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Для нанесения ударов были задействованы оперативно-тактическая авиация, ударные беспилотные летательные аппараты, ракетные войска и артиллерия. Также российские вооруженные силы атаковали пункты временной дислокации украинских военных и иностранных наемников в 142 районах.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ранее Министерство обороны России сообщило о нанесении массированных и групповых ударов по военным объектам на территории Украины. В результате атак пострадали предприятия военной промышленности, аэродромы, места хранения и запуска беспилотных летательных аппаратов и безэкипажных катеров, а также объекты топливно-энергетического, транспортного и портового комплексов. Кроме того, были поражены пункты временной дислокации украинских вооруженных формирований и наемников.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ранее 5-tv.ru сообщал, что президент России Владимир Путин поручил Министерству обороны представить свои предложения в связи с ударом ВСУ по колледжу в Старобельске ЛНР. Глава государства подчеркнул, что одними заявлениями МИДа в подобных случаях ограничиться невозможно.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Еще больше новостей — у Пятого канала в мессенджере МАКС.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Российские военные нанесли удар по предприятию ВПК и объектам энергетики Украины','','publish','open','open','','%d1%80%d0%be%d1%81%d1%81%d0%b8%d0%b9%d1%81%d0%ba%d0%b8%d0%b5-%d0%b2%d0%be%d0%b5%d0%bd%d0%bd%d1%8b%d0%b5-%d0%bd%d0%b0%d0%bd%d0%b5%d1%81%d0%bb%d0%b8-%d1%83%d0%b4%d0%b0%d1%80-%d0%bf%d0%be-%d0%bf','','','2026-05-23 14:14:30','2026-05-23 14:14:30','',0,'https://ongoingstoriesofmysoul.org/onehandclapping/?p=248',0,'post','',0),
